0not%20great%2C%20at%20all%20of%20your%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20Justin%20some%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20thrive%20as%20an%20overemployed%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20worked%20four%20remote%20jobs%20simultaneously%20for%20seven%20months%20until%20one%20of%20them%2C%20a%20contract%20role%2C%20was%20terminated.%20While%20he%20earned%20well%20over%20six%20figures%20during%20this%20seven-month%20span%2C%20he%20said%20losing%20the%20fourth%20job%20was%20almost%20a%20relief%20%E2%80%94%20because%20his%20work%20life%20was%20becoming%20unsustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20money%20was%20phenomenal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it%20felt%20like%20almost%20every%20day%20was%20a%20challenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20said%20that%20secretly%20juggling%20three%20full-time%20jobs%2C%20each%20of%20which%20pays%20over%20six%20figures%20annually%2C%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bfairly%20easy.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20his%20typical%20workday%20is%20from%207%3A30%20a.m.%20to%205%3A00%20p.m.%2C%20but%20that%20he's%20usually%20only%20busy%20about%20five%20hours%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20Justin%20has%20studied%20all%20the%20excuses%20for%20missing%20meetings%2C%20not%20turning%20his%20computer%20camera%20on%2C%20and%20not%20being%20available%20for%20extra%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ework%20tasks.%20But%20his%20top%20piece%20of%20advice%20for%20overemployed%20workers%20is%20to%20be%20good%2C%20not%20great%2C%20at%20all%20of%20your%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20be%20good%20at%20one's%20job%20so%20your%20bosses%20don't%20suspect%20anything%2C%20he%20said.%20For%20some%20workers%2C%20this%20might%20mean%20focusing%20on%20just%20two%20jobs%20rather%20than%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlways%20be%20available%2C%20respond%20promptly%2C%20and%20do%20good%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20deadlines%2C%20and%20if%20you%20can't%2C%20communicate%20that%20ahead%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20not%20be%20%26quot%3Bgreat%26quot%3B%20at%20one's%20job%20to%20avoid%20the%20extra%20responsibilities%20that%20could%20come%20with%20a%20promotion%2C%20Justin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20also%20results%20in%20his%20bosses%20expecting%20less%20of%20him%20and%20not%20overwhelming%20him%20with%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20managers%20at%20two%20of%20my%20jobs%20ask%20me%20if%20I%20need%20help%20or%20additional%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thank%20them%20for%20their%20concern%2C%20say%20everything%20is%20under%20control%2C%20but%20I%20promise%20to%20let%20them%20know%20if%20I%20need%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20what%20you've%20learned%20at%20one%20job%20to%20become%20more%20productive%20at%20the%20others%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20said%20he's%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20avoid%20meeting%20conflicts%20and%20join%20multiple%20meetings%20simultaneously%20when%20necessary.%20His%20biggest%20obstacles%20are%20impromptu%20calls%20from%20his%20bosses%20that%20he%20can't%20plan%20for.%20When%20group%20meetings%20that%20include%20his%20bosses%20are%20double-booked%2C%20he%20said%20they're%20sometimes%20a%20blessing%20in%20disguise%20%E2%80%94%20as%20he%20knows%20he%20won't%20receive%20a%20surprise%20call%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20Justin%20said%20working%20multiple%20jobs%20that%20are%20similar%20has%20made%20him%20more%20productive%20at%20each%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20this%20has%20been%20a%20big%20time%20saver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20new%20issue%20happens%20at%20job%20one%2C%20it's%20almost%20a%20guarantee%20that%20job%20two%20or%20job%20three%20will%20see%20that%20same%20issue%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20they%20do%2C%20I%20can%20cut%20that%20research%20time%20down%20from%20a%20week%20or%20more%2