l%20life%20by%20watching%20how%20their%20colleagues%20behaved%20in%20the%20office%2C%20Gen%20Z%20has%20been%20largely%20left%20to%20their%20own%20devices.%20That%20lack%20of%20on-the-job%20coaching%2C%20combined%20with%20layoffs%20and%20the%20effects%20of%20inflation%2C%20has%20left%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20feeling%20on%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F404174%2Feconomic-cost-poor-employee-mental-health.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20workers%20ages%2018%20to%2029%20reported%20that%20their%20job%20had%20negatively%20affected%20their%20mental%20health.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20stress%20of%20the%20workplace%20manifests%20as%20a%20sense%20of%20ambivalence%20and%20withdrawal%20from%20their%20professional%20lives.%20Another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F404693%2Fgeneration-disconnected-data-gen-workplace.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Gen%20Z%20was%20the%20least%20engaged%20group%20in%20the%20workplace%20and%20the%20most%20burned%20out%20from%20their%20jobs.%20To%20cope%2C%20Gen%20Z%20employees%20are%20taking%20significantly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhrnews.co.uk%2Fgen-z-employees-are-taking-significantly-more-sick-days-than-their-older-peers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20sick%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20older%20peers%20%E2%80%94%20often%20due%20to%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4NMkp%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Work%20engagement%2C%20burnout%2C%20and%20stress%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnxious%20teams%2C%20as%20has%20been%20well%20documented%2C%20can%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20take%20risks%2C%20to%20innovate%2C%20and%20have%20low%20psychological%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20Morra%20Aarons-Mele%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Anxious%20Achiever%2C%26quot%3B%20said.%20In%20a%202021%20workplace%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadaa.org%2Fworkplace-stress-anxiety-disorders-survey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Anxiety%20and%20Depression%20Association%20of%20America%2C%2056%25%20of%20surveyed%20employees%20said%20that%20anxiety%20affected%20their%20job%20performance.%20Half%20said%20it%20had%20negatively%20influenced%20their%20relationships%20with%20coworkers%2C%20and%2043%25%20said%20it%20had%20affected%20their%20relationships%20with%20superiors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202025%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20poised%20to%20represent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2022%2F05%2Fgen-z-don-t-want-to-work-for-you-here-s-how-to-change-their-mind%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E27%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20workforce%20in%20leading%20Western%20countries%20and%20a%20full%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fpages%2Fconsumer-business%2Farticles%2Funderstanding-generation-z-in-the-workplace.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-third%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20global%20population.%20If%20a%20significant%20majority%20of%20the%20cohort%20remains%20too%20stressed%20to%20effectively%20participate%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20experts%20say%20there%20could%20be%20devastating%20consequences%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20in%20economic%20terms%20but%20also%20from%20a%20social%20and%20broader%20societal%20perspective.%20Already%2C%20missed%20work%20and%20lost%20productivity%20cost%20the%20US%20economy%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.nylas.com%2Ft1%2F10%2F91xkgv28yn2gmvhffnqp4vivp%2F0%2F91c8e1c1fe855d8c59f30d747b73229f752d814d21120b61e074ed5744deafe3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2447%20billion%20each%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I%20don't%20really%20know%20the%20protocol'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Cloey%20Callahan%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%202020%2C%20she%20began%20working%20remotely%20as%20a%20contracted%20reporter%20for%20various%20newspapers%20in%20upstate%20New%20York.%20Now%20at%2025%2C%20she%20works%20as%20a%20senior%20reporter%20at%20the%20media%20company%20WorkLife%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20still%20remote.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20in%20college%2C%20I%20did%20a%20lot%20of%20internships%2C%20so%20I%20feel%20like%20that%20did%20help%20me%20prepare%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20without%20any%20other%20in-office%20experience%2C%20she%20said%20she%20got%20anxious%20about%20things%20such%20as%20not%20knowing%20how%20her%20peers%20went%20about%20their%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20emailing%20people%20all%20the%20time.%20I'm%20Slack%20messaging%20people%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThen%20I%20get%20anxious%3A%20'Am%20I%20being%20too%20much%3F%20Am%20I%20slacking%20someone%20too%20much%3F'%20I%20don't%20really%20know%20the%20protocol%2C%20as%20I%20have%20never%20been%20in%20an%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20using%20meetings%20with%20her%20manager%20to%20focus%20on%20career%20progression%2C%20Callahan%20finds%20that%20she%20spends%20the%20time%20comparing%20herself%20with%20other%20people%20and%20listing%20the%20worries%20that%20have%20been%20on%20her%20mind.%20While%20Gen%20Z's%20openness%20about%20their%20feelings%20can%20be%20helpful%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20some%20bosses%20say%20that%20it%20is%20also%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20younger%20employees'%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20millennial%20boss%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-manage-boss-gen-z-workers-feelings-work-employees2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20one%20of%20her%20biggest%20challenges%20with%20young%20employees%20was%20their%20many%20feelings%20about%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20I%20applaud%20his%20willingness%20to%20share%20how%20he%20feels%2C%20and%20I%20marvel%20at%20how%20comfortable%20he%20is%20in%20saying%20what%20he%20thinks%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20about%20one%20of%20her%20reports.%20%26quot%3BBut%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20as%20a%20boss%2C%20it's%20not%20my%20job%20to%20help%20him%20work%20through%20all%20his%20feelings%20%E2%80%94%20only%20the%20ones%20related%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20open%20about%20feelings%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharing-at-work-stop-oversharing-in-office-professional-growth-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoversharing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20leave%20managers%20struggling%20to%20help%20anxious%20new%20hires%20keep%20calm.%20Callahan%20herself%20acknowledged%20that%20focusing%20on%20her%20anxieties%20during%20her%20manager%20check-ins%20was%20probably%20not%20the%20best%20use%20of%20her%20time.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20trying%20to%20be%20more%20mindful%20of%20it%20and%20set%20boundaries%20with%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELou%20Ali%2C%2041%2C%20who%20manages%20Malcolmson%20and%20another%20Gen%20Z%20employee%20at%20the%20PR%20agency%20Honcho%2C%20said%20she%20was%20puzzled%20by%20what%20she%20saw%20as%20the%20paradox%20of%20Gen%20Z's%20workplace%20anxiety.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20Ali%20told%20me%2C%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20come%20across%20as%20confident.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20that%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20bravado%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20underneath%20the%20strong%20exterior%2C%20Ali%20has%20noticed%20that%20many%20younger%20employees%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20their%20place%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BActually%2C%20they've%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20self-esteem%20issues%20or%20uncertainty%20about%20career%20progression.%26quot%3B%20Ali%20has%20noticed%20that%20if%20career%20progression%20doesn't%20happen%20right%20away%20for%20her%20younger%20reports%2C%20it%20knocks%20their%20confidence%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20wonder%20what%20they've%20done%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20frustrations%2C%20most%20managers%20grant%20their%20young%20workers%20some%20grace.%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20go%20to%20the%20office%20every%20single%20day%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Ali%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20speak%20to%20my%20peers%20about%20my%20anxieties%2C%20whereas%20younger%20workers%20don't%20really%20have%20that.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20don't%20know.%20If%20you're%20not%20surrounded%20by%20people%20and%20picking%20up%20on%20little%20things%2C%20how%20do%20you%20know%20to%20ask%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrappling%20with%20uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20core%20of%20Gen%20Z's%20worries%20about%20work%20comes%20down%20to%20uncertainty%2C%20experts%20told%20me.%20The%20natural%20uneasiness%20that%20comes%20with%20starting%20a%20new%20chapter%20of%20life%20was%20compounded%20by%20the%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20and%20the%20chaos%20of%20a%20new%20work%20paradigm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnxiety%20is%20driven%20by%20uncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20Ellen%20Hendriksen%2C%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Be%20Yourself%3A%20Quiet%20Your%20Inner%20Critic%20and%20Rise%20Above%20Social%20Anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20said.%20Because%20they%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20digital%20age%20with%20nearly%20unlimited%20amounts%20of%20information%20at%20their%20fingertips%2C%20Hendriksen%20said%2C%20Gen%20Z%20has%20the%20least%20experience%20with%20uncertainty.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20need%20to%20know%20where%20to%20go%2C%20you%20can%20pull%20up%20Google%20Maps%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20going%20to%20a%20new%20restaurant%2C%20you%20can%20look%20at%20the%20menu%20ahead%20of%20time.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20certainty%20in%20this%20world%20now%20which%20didn't%20exist%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20work%2C%20there's%20often%20a%20lack%20of%20certainty%20%E2%80%94%20which%20gets%20exacerbated%20in%20a%20remote%20workplace%20where%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20avoid%20confrontation.%20%26quot%3BAnxiety%20is%20maintained%20by%20avoidance%2C%26quot%3B%20Henriksen%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20first%20reaction%20when%20we%20are%20anxious%20is%20often%20to%20avoid%20the%20thing%20that%20is%20making%20us%20scared%2C%20and%20so%20if%20we%20are%20anxious%20about%20speaking%20in%20a%20meeting%2C%20we%20might%20remain%20silent.%20If%20we%20are%20anxious%20about%20taking%20phone%20calls%2C%20we'll%20let%20those%20calls%20go%20to%20voicemail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20experience%20navigating%20uncertainty%20has%20contributed%20to%20what%20Michelle%20P.%20King%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BHow%20Work%20Works%2C%26quot%3B%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3Bambiguity%20skills%20gap.%26quot%3B%20King%20said%20this%20showed%20up%20in%20two%20ways%20for%20younger%20generations%3A%20%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20it%20is%20ambiguity%20in%20tasks%2C%20like%20solving%20problems%20that%20don't%20have%20a%20clear-cut%20solution%2C%20working%20on%20complex%20tasks%20with%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20novelty%2C%20and%20creative%20thinking%20on%20the%20fly.%26quot%3B%20As%20a%20result%2C%20a%20number%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20struggling%20to%20manage%20how%20their%20work%20gets%20done%20and%20lack%20confidence%20in%20making%20decisions%20at%20work%20without%20all%20the%20necessary%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20impact%20is%20on%20social%20interactions.%20This%20year%20King%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20OnePoll%2C%20surveyed%202%2C000%20Gen%20Zers%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20US.%20In%20the%20study%2C%2030%25%20of%20respondents%20ages%2018%20to%2024%20reported%20increased%20stress%20over%20ambiguous%20relationships%20at%20work%2C%20with%20nine%20in%2010%20saying%20they%20avoided%20in-person%20events%20because%20of%20social%20anxiety%2C%20and%20nearly%20one-quarter%20saying%20they%20were%20uncomfortable%20speaking%20up%20in%20team%20meetings%20and%20sharing%20their%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20new%20world%20of%20work%2C%20we%20have%20to%20manage%20how%20we%20work%20with%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%2C%20knowing%20how%20to%20interpret%20other%20people's%20feelings%20and%20intentions%20so%20that%20you%20can%20manage%20your%20informal%20interactions%20with%20them.%20Whether%20sensing%20when%20a%20presentation%20has%20gone%20on%20too%20long%20or%20understanding%20the%20subtext%20of%20what%20someone%20is%20saying%2C%20managing%20how%20you%20work%20is%20a%20fundamental%20skill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBosses%2C%20who%20had%20plenty%20of%20practice%20building%20their%20soft%20skills%20in%20the%20office%2C%20have%20their%20role%20to%20play%20in%20helping%20their%20youngest%20workers.%20%26quot%3BManagers%20need%20to%20close%20this%20skill%20gap%20by%20providing%20ongoing%20coaching%20and%20feedback%20that%20equip%20graduates%20to%20do%20their%20jobs%20without%20having%20all%20the%20information%2C%20respond%20to%20constant%20changes%20at%20work%2C%20and%20learn%20how%20to%20adapt%20their%20communication%20style%20to%20connect%20with%20different%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20anxiety%20at%20work%20may%20be%20nothing%20new%2C%20the%20workplace%20itself%20has%20been%20turned%20on%20its%20head%20in%20recent%20years.%20%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20think%20there%20has%20always%20been%20a%20'young%20person%20in%20the%20workforce%20wanting%20to%20do%20well'%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20Malcolmson%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20now%20it%20just%20feels%20so%20much%20more%20intense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa