out%20that%20both%20bears%20the%20brunt%20of%20climate-induced%20calamities%20and%20holds%20the%20key%20to%20transformative%20solutions.%20That%20is%2C%20women%2C%20girls%2C%20and%20marginalised%20communities.%20As%20the%20echoes%20of%20the%20G20%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20reverberate%2C%20underscoring%20the%20crucial%20role%20of%20women%20in%20climate%20response%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20for%20COP28%20to%20not%20merely%20acknowledge%20but%20prioritise%20the%20gender-specific%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%20Recognizing%20that%20vulnerabilities%20are%20far%20from%20evenly%20distributed%2C%20a%20robust%20commitment%20to%20inclusivity%20must%20underscore%20global%20climate%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESkewed%20numbers%20tell%20a%20poignant%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20staggering%20statistics%3A%20women%20and%20children%20are%2014%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20lose%20their%20lives%20during%20natural%20disasters%20compared%20to%20men.%20The%20aftermath%20of%20the%202004%20Indian%20Ocean%20Tsunami%2C%20where%2070%25%20of%20the%20230%2C000%20lives%20lost%20were%20women%2C%20serves%20as%20a%20stark%20illustration%20of%20this%20gendered%20impact.%20In%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region%20alone%2C%20over%20100%20million%20people%20are%20affected%20annually%2C%20while%20India%20itself%20grapples%20with%20an%20annual%20average%20of%20USD%20240%20million%20in%20damages%20caused%20by%20floods.%20This%20complex%20interplay%20of%20climate%20issues%20and%20gender%20inequality%20demands%20our%20urgent%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowhere%20is%20this%20more%20evident%20than%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20agriculture%2C%20where%20women%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20cultivation%2C%20harvesting%2C%20and%20distribution.%20Though%20they%20make%20up%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20global%20agricultural%20workforce%2C%20women%20own%20less%20than%2020%25%20of%20the%20land.%20This%20stark%20disparity%20in%20access%20to%20resources%20not%20only%20impedes%20women's%20resilience%20during%20disasters%20but%20also%20amplifies%20the%20challenges%20posed%20by%20climate%20change.%C2%A0Extreme%20weather%20events%20also%20take%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20health%20and%20well-being%20of%20women%20and%20children.%20From%20the%20increased%20risk%20of%20stillbirths%20due%20to%20extreme%20heat%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20vector-borne%20diseases%20like%20dengue%20and%20Zika%20virus%2C%20the%20repercussions%20are%20severe.%20Climate%20change%20also%20contributes%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20gender-based%20violence%2C%20reduces%20access%20to%20essential%20services%2C%20and%20diminishes%20opportunities%20for%20education%20and%20economic%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHumanitarian%20interventions%2C%20while%20well%20intentioned%2C%20often%20adhere%20to%20norms%20aligned%20with%20traditional%20body%20types%20or%20gender%20roles%2C%20neglecting%20the%20unique%20needs%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20or%20those%20identifying%20with%20different%20genders.%20This%20oversight%20further%20marginalises%20already%20invisible%20groups%2C%20deepening%20existing%20inequalities%20and%20hindering%20effective%20responses%20to%20climate-induced%20crises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20face%20of%20these%20formidable%20challenges%2C%20it's%20crucial%20to%20recognize%20that%20women%20are%20not%20just%20survivors%20but%20pivotal%20actors%20in%20climate%20change%20solutions.%20They%20must%20lead%20the%20way%20in%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20efforts%2C%20drawing%20on%20their%20nuanced%20understanding%20of%20local%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20has%20been%20proactive%20in%20addressing%20climate%20change%2C%20with%20ambitious%20commitments%20to%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20increase%20the%20share%20of%20non-fossil%20fuel%20energy.%20And%20initiatives%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3EPradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20India%2C%20providing%20vulnerable%20women%20with%20clean%20cooking%20gas%2C%20showcase%20the%20potential%20for%20gender-sensitive%20climate%20action%20that%20addresses%20both%20environmental%20and%20societal%20concerns.%20Efforts%20like%20%3Cem%3E'Har%20Ghar%20Jal'%3C%2Fem%3E%20aim%20to%20provide%20tap%20water%20to%20every%20rural%20household%20by%202024%2C%20alleviating%20the%20care%20burden%20on%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20during%20a%20cyclone%20preparedness%20drill%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Odisha%2C%20a%20state%20with%20a%20strong%20record%20of%20managing%20disasters%2C%20Gyana%20Ranjan%20Das%2C%20the%20Managing%20Director%20of%20the%20Odisha%20State%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%20(OSDMA)%2C%20observed%20that%20women%20and%20girls%20are%20playing%20a%20more%20central%20role%20in%20managing%20crises.%20The%20women%20and%20girls%20have%20been%20provided%20special%20training%20and%20support%20for%20disaster%20preparedness%20and%20response%20through%20a%20UNFPA%20project.%20Despite%20such%20gender%20transformative%20occurrences%2C%20persistent%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20political%20inequalities%20still%20hinder%20the%20full%20realisation%20of%20women's%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPriority%20Actions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gendered-impact%20of%20National%20Determined%20Contributions%20(NDCs)%20of%20countries%20needs%20better%20scrutiny.%20For%20example%2C%20only%20a%20fraction%20incorporates%20aspects%20of%20sexual%20and%20reproductive%20health%20and%20rights.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20United%20Nations%20Framework%20Convention%20on%20Climate%20Change%20emphasises%20the%20need%20for%20public%20and%20private%20financing%20to%20incorporate%20gender%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInclusive%20digital%20solutions%20can%20enhance%20early%20warning%20and%20post-climate%20relief%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20need%20to%20accelerate%20digital%20public%20infrastructure%20accessibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen's%20leadership%20on%20climate%20action%20will%20matter%20not%20just%20as%20elected%20representatives%20but%20also%20as%20members%20of%20local%20government.%20Much%20more%20can%20be%20achieved%20by%20engaging%20with%20women's%20collectives%20at%20the%20local%20level%20who%20face%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20embracing%20democratic%20engagement%20and%20prioritising%20gender-responsive%20disaster%20preparedness%2C%20we%20can%20create%20a%20world%20where%20women%20and%20girls%20not%20only%20survive%20disasters%20but%20thrive%20-%20a%20world%20where%20their%20voices%20are%20amplified%2C%20their%20dignity%20is%20assured%2C%20and%20their%20contributions%20are%20celebrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20the%20imperative%20for%20COP28%20and%20global%20climate%20governance%20is%20clear%20-%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20inclusive%20approach%20is%20non-negotiable.%20The%20Gender%20Equality%20Day%20at%20COP28%20is%20an%20acknowledgment%20that%20climate%20justice%20demands%20gender%20justice.%20The%20destiny%20of%20our%20planet%20is%20intricately%20linked%20with%20the%20empowerment%20and%20resilience%20of%20women%20and%20marginalised%20communities.%20Only%20through%20collective%20and%20gender-sensitive%20efforts%20can%20we%20navigate%20the%20stormy%20seas%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20build%20a%20world%20where%20everyone%20not%20only%20survives%20but%20thrives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shombi%20Sharp%20is%20United%20Nations%20Resident%20Coordinator%2C%20Andrea%20M.%20Wojnar%20is%20India%20Representative%20United%20Nations%20Population%20Fund%20and%20Atul%20Bagai%20is%20India%20Country%20Head%2C%20United%20Nations%20Environment%20Programme.%20The%20authors%20are%20part%20of%20the%20UN%20in%20India%20Country%20Team%2C%20collectively%20delivering%20on%20the%20SDGs%20in%20partnership%20with%20India.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702289760000%2C