0J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Srinagar%2C%20has%20lost%20nearly%208%25%20forest%20cover%2C%20a%20new%20study%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFunded%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20under%20the%20National%20Mission%20for%20Himalayan%20Studies%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20Dal%20Lake%20in%20Srinagar%20city%20and%20other%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20catchment%20area%20of%20DNP%20have%20nearly%20halved%20in%20size%2C%20from%2019.82%20sq%20km%20to%2010.62%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20a%20model-based%20analysis%20of%20data%2C%20topographic%20maps%20and%20ground%20situation%20from%201965%20to%202020%2C%20warns%20that%20these%20changes%20are%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20fragmentation%20of%20natural%20habitats%E2%80%9D%20which%20will%20have%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20biodiversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peer-reviewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10661-023-11676-x%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20appeared%20in%20the%20September%20issue%20of%20the%20journal%20%3Cem%3ESpringer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20painting%20a%20grim%20picture%20of%20the%20land%20use%20changes%20in%20Dachigam%20which%20is%20located%20in%20the%20Zabarwan%20Range%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20and%20is%20home%20to%20the%20Kashmiri%20stag%20(Hangul)%20among%20other%20endemic%20and%20critically%20endangered%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20an%20official%20study%20has%20concluded%20that%20not%20only%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20but%20its%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20zone%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20protected%20area%20where%20human%20intervention%20is%20illegal%20%E2%80%93%20has%20also%20reduced%2C%20both%20outside%20the%20park%20and%20within%2C%20by%20more%20than%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20designation%20of%20DNP%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98protected%20area%E2%80%99%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20prevented%20habitat%20loss%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20the%20pastures%20and%20shrub-lands%20in%20the%20park%20will%20grow%20by%2048%25%20and%2037%25%20respectively%20while%20the%20forest%20cover%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20change%20much%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocated%20some%2022%20km%20from%20Srinagar%20city%20centre%20Lal%20Chowk%2C%20Dachigam%20Park%20and%20its%20catchment%20areas%20are%20spread%20across%20337%20sq%20km%20in%20the%20eastern%20part%20of%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20serving%20not%20just%20as%20a%20habitat%20for%20some%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20richest%20biodiversity%20but%20also%20as%20a%20quaint%20getaway%20for%20adventure%20lovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDachigam%20used%20to%20be%20a%20residential%20area%20before%20World%20War%201.%20As%20wild%20animals%20were%20frequently%20sighted%20there%2C%20the%20then%20Dogra%20rulers%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20vacated%20the%20inhabitants%20of%20ten%20villages%20there%20and%20converted%20it%20into%20a%20hunting%20reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reserve%2C%20which%20was%20declared%20a%20protected%20area%20in%201910%2C%20has%20thick%20coniferous%20forests%2C%20undulating%20pastures%20and%20gurgling%20water%20streams%20flowing%20down%20the%20mountains%20that%20not%20only%20sustain%20the%20Himalayan%20biodiversity%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20herding%20communities%20but%20also%20bring%20drinking%20water%20supply%20to%20Srinagar%20city%20from%20the%20high%20altitude%20alpine%20lakes%20of%20Lidder%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221149%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul.jpg%201149w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151954%2Fhangul-1024x642.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688645%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20herd%20of%20Hangul%20(Kashmiri%20stag)%20in%20Dachigam.%20Photo%3A%20Tahirshawl%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2055-year%20study%2C%20which%20also%20analysed%20the%20United%20States%20Geological%20Survey%E2%80%99s%20(USGS)%20earth%20observation%20data%2C%20notes%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20proper%20%E2%80%9Cland%20use%20policy%E2%80%9D%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20accompanied%20by%20rapid%20and%20unplanned%20urbanisation%20raises%20troubling%20questions%20about%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20believe%20that%20the%20loss%20of%20habitat%20will%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20of%20man-animal%20conflicts%20and%20it%20may%20also%20have%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20Hangul%2C%20which%20is%20accorded%20the%20highest%20protection%20under%20Schedule%20I%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Act%2C%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrfan%20Rashid%2C%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Geoinformatics%20Department%2C%20said%20that%20the%20degradation%20of%20land%20cover%20can%20have%20serious%20implications%20not%20just%20for%20DNP%2C%20which%20was%20declared%20a%20national%20park%20in%201981%2C%20but%20also%20for%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20which%20is%20located%20downstream%20of%20the%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20reduction%20in%20green%20cover%20would%20increase%20the%20silt%20load%20in%20the%20stream%20that%20ultimately%20pours%20out%20into%20Dal%20lake.%20This%20would%20lead%20to%20enrichment%20of%20Nitrogen%20and%20Phosphorus%20in%20lake%E2%80%99s%20waters%2C%20a%20process%20called%20eutrophication%2C%20that%20has%20immense%20implications%20for%20lake%20water%20quality%2C%20biota%20and%20aesthetics%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rashid%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study%E2%80%99s%20authors%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20comes%20out%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change%20told%20parliament%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetailm.aspx%3FPRID%3D1906388%5C%22%3EMarch%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20forest%20cover%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20increased%20marginally%20by%200.14%25%20since%202019.%20According%20to%20official%20data%2C%2039.15%25%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20forest%20area%2C%20spanning%2021%2C387%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnsustainable%20development%20and%20unregulated%20human%20footprint%20have%20accelerated%20climate%20change%20which%20is%20feared%20to%20cause%20irreversible%20damage%20to%20the%20mountain%20ecosystem%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Himalayas.%20Experts%20believe%20that%20the%20diminishing%20size%20of%20Dachigam%20will%20shrink%20its%20natural%20habitats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20serious%20concern%20is%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20incidence%20of%20human-wildlife%20conflicts%20which%20are%20becoming%20more%20frequent%20all%20across%20Kashmir%20since%20a%20lot%20of%20infrastructure%20development%20(roads%2C%20buildings)%20is%20happening%20in%20otherwise%20natural%20forested%20landscapes.%20Other%20issues%20could%20be%20increased%20nutrient%20enrichment%20of%20waters%20from%20domestic%20sewage%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rashid%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproached%20for%20comment%2C%20a%20senior%20officer%20in%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20administration%20referred%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20Regional%20Wildlife%20Warden%2C%20Kashmir%2C%20Rashid%20Yahya%20Naqash%2C%20who%20sought%20to%20question%20the%20methodology%20used%20in%20the%20study%20while%20also%20rejecting%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20no%20negative%20change%20in%20Dachigam.%20The%20park%20is%20healthy%20and%20there%20are%20several%20studies%20which%20have%20found%20that%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20has%20increased%20over%20the%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yahya%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20a%2030-year%20study%20from%201989%20to%202019%20which%20suggests%20that%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20has%20increased%20by%20between%2014.91%25%20and%2016.96%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20to%20him%20that%20the%20latest%20study%20was%20based%20on%20scientific%20data%20and%20ground%20validation%2C%20and%20that%20officials%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Department%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20were%20part%20of%20the%20study%2C%20Naqash%20sought%20more%20time%20before%20responding.%20Later%2C%20both%20the%20officials%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20park%20has%20lost%20six%20sq%20km%20or%20close%20to%208%25%20of%20its%20forest%20cover%20in%2055%20years%20while%20the%20%E2%80%98exposed%20rock%E2%80%99%20area%20reduced%20by%204.26%20sq%20km%20(13%25)%20from%2027.28%20sq%20km%20to%2023.02%20sq%20km.%20However%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20the%20reduction%20in%20forest%20cover%20has%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20shrublands%20which%20grew%20by%207.3%20sq%20km%20(56.28%25)%20while%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20alpine%20pasture%20increased%20by%208.02%20sq%20km%20(31.89%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20has%20also%20found%20that%20the%20land%20around%20the%20park%20under%20agriculture%20shrank%20by%2075.16%25%20(from%2040.02%20sq%20km%20in%201965%20to%20merely%209.94%20sq%20km%20in%202020)%20and%20alpine%20pasture%20nearly%20halved%20by%2046.68%25%20or%205.28%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20three-fold%20increase%20(326%25)%20or%2024.66%20sq%20km%20expansion%20of%20the%20built-up%20area%20around%20the%20park%2C%20which%20includes%20orchards%2C%20and%20residential%20and%20commercial%20areas%2C%20while%20aquatic%20vegetation%20outside%20the%20park%20expanded%20by%20174%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20points%20out%20that%20the%20water-intensive%20croplands%20around%20DNP%20shrunk%20by%2075%25%20in%20the%2055-year%20study%20period%20and%20they%20have%20been%20replaced%20either%20by%20built-up%20areas%20or%20apple%20orchards%2C%20a%20trend%20which%20is%20projected%20to%20accelerate%20in%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702288829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11151838%2FSarband-kashmir.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjk-dachigam-national-park-grim-picture-forest-cover%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20park%2C%20located%20near%20Srinagar%2C%20lost%208%25%20of%20its%20forest%20cover%20in%2055%20years%20while%20the%20%E2%80%98exposed%20rock%E2%80%99%20area%20reduced%20by%2013%25.%20There%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20park%E2%80%99s%20shrublands%20and%20alpine%20pastures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjk-dachigam-national-park-grim-picture-forest-cover%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98How%20to%20Have%20Sex%E2%80%99%20Star%20Mia%20McKenna-Bruce%2C%20Louisa%20Connolly-Burnham%2C%20Michael%20Fox%20to%20Lead%20Queer%20Drama%20%E2%80%98Sister%20Wives%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702288800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FMia-Mckenna-Bruce-Louisa-Connolly-Burnham-Mia-Mckenna-Bruce.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235832395%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mia%20McKenna-Bruce%20(BIFA%20winner%20for%20%E2%80%9CHow%20to%20Have%20Sex%E2%80%9D)%2C%2