%20Kabaddi%2C%20and%20chess%20gained%20interest.%20Indian%20films%2C%20songs%2C%20and%20actors%20received%20global%20attention%2C%20along%20with%20local%20OTT%20content%20and%20memes.%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20local%20trips%20were%20popular%20travel%20destinations%2C%20while%20regional%20culinary%20delights%20like%20Mango%20pickle%20and%20Rava%20Ladoo%20were%20searched%20for%20recipes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fgoogle-year-in-search-what-india-searched-most-for-in-the-year-2023%2Farticleshow%2F105895621.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Cause%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Victories%20in%20State%20Polls%20Is%20Mundane.%20Misreading%20It%20Will%20Only%20Benefit%20Them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04152158%2FGALn98pbMAAFBeo.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20(BJP%E2%80%99s)%20jubilation%20over%20its%20victories%20in%20the%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20elections%2C%20and%20the%20near-panic%20that%20defeat%20has%20sown%20in%20the%20Congress%2C%20are%20measures%20of%20the%20increasing%20fragility%20of%20our%20democratic%20system.%20It%20shows%20that%20even%20after%2016%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20innumerable%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20neither%20party%E2%80%99s%20leaders%2C%20nor%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20media%20pundits%20understand%20how%20the%20simple%20majority%20voting%20system%20(SMS)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20our%20constitution%20makers%20adopted%20in%201948%20%E2%80%93%20works.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20the%20Congress%20understood%20this%2C%20it%20would%20have%20known%20from%20the%20start%20that%20the%20elections%20were%20likely%20to%20swing%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20way%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20possibly%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20for%20exactly%20the%20same%20reason%20they%20had%20swung%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20way%20in%202018.%20This%20reason%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20that%20political%20scientists%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20studied%20Indian%20politics%2C%20have%20labelled%20the%20%E2%80%9Canti-incumbency%20factor%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20anti-incumbency%20factor%20is%20no%20more%20than%20an%20accumulation%20of%20disenchantment%20with%20the%20ruling%20government%20that%20arises%20when%20it%20fails%20to%20meet%20the%20expectations%20of%20all%20of%20those%20who%20voted%20for%20it%20in%20the%20previous%20elections.%20This%20makes%20a%20proportion%20of%20them%20decide%20to%20try%20their%20luck%20with%20the%20other%20side%20in%20the%20next%20election.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20impact%20of%20the%20anti-incumbency%20factor%20is%20much%20greater%20in%20the%20SMS%20than%20it%20is%20in%20proportional%20representation.%20This%20is%20because%20it%20invariably%20magnifies%20the%20ratio%20of%20seats%20won%20by%20the%20largest%20party%20to%20the%20votes%20cast%20for%20it%20and%20correspondingly%20reduces%20it%20for%20all%20the%20remaining%20parties.%20In%20the%20theoretical%20limiting%20case%2C%20where%20the%20vote%20is%20equally%20divided%20between%20all%20contending%20parties%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20even%200.1%25%20in%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20one%20party%20will%20give%20it%20100%25%20of%20the%20seats.%20The%20seat-to-vote%20magnification%20then%20is%20close%20to%20infinite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F687497%2Fthree-things-bjps-definitive-victory-in-the-assembly-elections-tells-us%2F%5C%22%3EThree%20Things%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Definitive%20Victory%20in%20the%20Assembly%20Elections%20Tells%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESMS%20has%20one%20important%20advantage%20over%20proportional%20representation%2C%20the%20other%20widely%20used%20system%20of%20voting%20in%20democracies.%20The%20advantage%20is%20that%20the%20compression%20of%20seats%20in%20relation%20to%20votes%20gets%20more%20pronounced%20as%20the%20political%20parties%20get%20smaller.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20forces%20the%20fringe%20parties%20to%20merge%20with%20their%20closest%20ideological%20neighbours%20in%20order%20to%20retain%20some%20say%20in%20policy%20making.%20This%20need%20for%20compromise%20discourages%20the%20adoption%20of%20ideological%20%E2%80%93%20as%20distinct%20from%20pragmatic%20%E2%80%93%20programmes%20of%20governance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20democracy%20matures%2C%20this%20creates%20a%20two-party%20system%20in%20which%20both%20parties%20have%20shed%20extreme%20ideological%20positions%20in%20order%20to%20woo%20the%20uncommitted%20vote%20at%20the%20centre.%20In%20a%20fully%20mature%20system%2C%20therefore%2C%20even%20a%20small%20increase%20in%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20one%20party%20enables%20it%20to%20win%20a%20disproportionately%20larger%20number%20of%20seats.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20is%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20elections%20this%20year.%20In%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20115%20seats%20against%2073%20in%202018%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20over%2060%25.%20But%20this%20was%20brought%20about%20by%20a%20mere%202.3%25%20rise%20in%20its%20vote%20share.%20The%20Congress%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20lost%2031%20of%20the%20100%20seats%20it%20had%20won%20in%202018%20despite%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20its%20share%20of%20the%20vote%20by%200.2%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20seats%20increased%20from%20109%20in%202018%20to%20163%20this%20year.%20While%20this%20increase%20came%20on%20the%20back%20of%20a%207.5%25%20rise%20in%20its%20vote%20share%2C%20the%20victory%20was%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20a%20large%20number%20of%20smaller%20parties%20as%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20vote%20share%20only%20fell%20by%200.5%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20table%20below%20shows%20that%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20there%20has%20been%20such%20anti-incumbency%20swings%20in%20these%20states.%20The%20Congress%20won%20the%20election%20in%20Rajasthan%20in%202008%2C%20lost%20it%20in%202013%2C%20won%20again%20in%202018%20and%20lost%20again%20this%20year.%20The%20BJP%20has%20shown%20the%20obverse%20pattern.%20The%20common%20feature%20of%20all%20the%20elections%20is%20the%20notable%20feature%20of%20all%20of%20these%20elections%20has%20been%20that%20small%20shifts%20in%20votes%20have%20caused%20huge%20gains%20and%20losses%20in%20seats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESeats%20won%20and%20vote%20shares%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20MP%20and%20Chhattisgarh%202008-18%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20border%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20cellpadding%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20cellspacing%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20data-sheets-root%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccolgroup%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%2271%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22108%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20data-sheets-value%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%3A2%2C%26quot%3B2%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3BYear%26quot%3B%7D%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EYear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%20data-sheets-value%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%3A3%2C%26quot%3B3%26quot%3B%3A2008%7D%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E2008%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%222%5