ars%20to%20clear%20the%20backlog%20of%20cases%20pending%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act%2C%20finds%20a%20new%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20the%20India%20Child%20Protection%20Fund%20(ICPF)%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Justice%20Awaits%3A%20An%20Analysis%20of%20the%20Efficacy%20of%20Justice%20Delivery%20Mechanisms%20in%20Cases%20of%20Child%20Sexual%20Abuse%20in%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20said%20that%20only%203%25%20of%20cases%20under%20the%20POCSO%20Act%20resulted%20in%20convictions%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Women%20and%20Child%20Development%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fover-2-26-lakh-pocso-cases-pending-in-fast-track-courts-up-has-over-60000-govt%5C%22%3Ehad%20in%202019%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20government%20would%20set%20up%20these%20fast-track%20courts%20using%20the%20%E2%80%98Nirbhaya%20Fund%E2%80%99.%20These%20courts%20were%20aimed%20at%20exclusively%20dealing%20with%20cases%20under%20POCSO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20legal%20and%20child%20rights%20experts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsetting-up-pocso-fast-track-courts-will-be-futile-unless-more-judges-are-appointed-justice-bv-nagarathna-216371%5C%22%3Ehad%20cautioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20merely%20setting%20up%20fast-track%20courts%20would%20not%20help%20unless%20more%20judges%20were%20appointed%20or%20public%20prosecutors%20trained%20and%20sensitised%20to%20deal%20with%20such%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20ICPF%20study%2C%20each%20of%20the%20over%201%2C000%20such%20courts%20in%20the%20country%20are%20clearing%20only%2028%20cases%20on%20average%20every%20year%2C%20falling%20short%20of%20the%20target%20of%20165%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ffast-track-courts-disposing-of-just-28-pocso-cases-per-year-on-average-research-paper%2Farticle67622192.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Maharashtra%2C%20it%20might%20take%20up%20to%202036%20for%20a%20child%20to%20get%20justice%20in%20a%20POCSO%20case.%20By%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20state%20had%2033%2C073%20such%20cases%20pending%20in%20the%20fast-track%20courts%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fover-243-lakh-pocso-cases-pending-in-fast-track-courts-till-jan-2023-3-conviction-rate-in-2022-report-2804200%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCurrently%252C%2520there%2520are%2520351%2520fast%2Cdisposed%2520of%25201%252C11%252C475%2520cases.%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20states%20such%20as%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar%2C%20it%20could%20take%20more%20than%2025%20years%20to%20bring%20the%20pending%20cases%20to%20closure%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20a%20complainant%20will%20have%20to%20wait%20till%202034%20as%20the%20state%20has%208%2C137%20pending%20cases%2C%20while%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Jharkhand%2C%20it%20will%20take%20till%202033%2C%20with%208%2C921%20and%204%2C408%20cases%2C%20respectively%2C%20the%20daily%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20on%20an%20average%2C%20only%2028%20POCSO%20cases%20were%20disposed%20of%20by%20each%20fast%20track%20special%20court%20(FTSC)%20in%202022.%20And%20India%20has%20a%20total%20of%202.43%20lakh%20POCSO%20cases%20pending%20in%20its%20fast%20track%20courts%2C%20as%20on%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20expenditure%20for%20the%20disposal%20of%20each%20case%20was%20Rs%202.73%20lakh%2C%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnataka%20(919)%20and%20Goa%20(62)%20are%20the%20two%20states%20with%20the%20least%20number%20of%20pending%20cases.%20A%20complainant%20can%20hope%20for%20justice%20by%202024%20in%20these%20states%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702276227000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc