a%20poet%20and%20as%20a%20writer%2C%20the%20two%20fields%20in%20which%20he%20made%20monumental%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%E2%80%99s%20warmth%2C%20his%20accessibility%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20lyrical%20genius%20%E2%80%93%20made%20him%20a%20household%20name%20and%20a%20national%20treasure.%20Hear%20him%2C%20in%202018%2C%20on%20BBC%20Radio%203%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fsounds%2Fplay%2Fp0695pcz%5C%22%3Ewaxing%20lyrical%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20his%20favourite%20Shakespearean%20moments.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20Caribbean%20and%20African%20folklore%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%E2%80%99s%20a%20character%20called%20Anansi%20who%E2%80%99s%20a%20spider%20and%20a%20bit%20of%20trickster%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20much%20like%20Puck.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESee%20him%20on%20a%20Channel%204%20chat%20show%20sofa%2C%20two%20years%20later%2C%20as%20MC%20Big%20Narstie%20asks%20why%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fracism-colonialism-and-slavery-why-empire-needs-to-be-removed-from-the-uk-honours-system-129311%5C%22%3Eturned%20down%20an%20OBE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99ve%20been%20fighting%20against%20empire%20all%20my%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20Zephaniah%20replies.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20could%20I%20then%20go%20and%20accept%20an%20honour%20which%20puts%20empire%20on%20to%20my%20name%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fd2PSoa8o3ps%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Benjamin%20Zephaniah%20On%20Why%20He%20TURNED%20DOWN%20His%20OBE%20%7C%20The%20Big%20Narstie%20Show%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20same%20attributes%20made%20Zephaniah%20the%20most%20prominent%20face%20of%20the%20UK%20Rastafari%20movement%2C%20in%20which%20he%20found%20his%20spiritual%20home.%20I%20had%20the%20privilege%20of%20getting%20to%20know%20him%20over%20the%20course%20of%20my%20research%20into%20Rastafari%20spirituality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20evergreen%20popularity%20of%20reggae%20music%20has%20resulted%20in%20public%20recognition%20of%20the%20Rastafari%20movement%20in%20name%2C%20in%20its%20beliefs%2C%20it%20remains%20misunderstood%20and%20mischaracterised.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20Zephaniah%20became%20its%20standard%20bearer.%20His%20public%20adherence%20represented%20a%20full%20frontal%20challenge%20to%20the%20pervasive%20criminal%20stereotypes%20with%20which%20racist%20politicians%20and%20police%20forces%20have%20long%20tagged%20Rastafari.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersecution%20of%20Rastafari%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20Handsworth%20area%20of%20Birmingham%20in%201958.%20He%20came%20of%20age%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20as%20the%20UK%20fell%20head%20first%20into%20Thatcherism%20and%20the%20far-right%20National%20Front%20achieved%20its%20biggest%20ever%20vote%20tally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlack%20Rastafari%20of%20the%20era%20invariably%20faced%20daily%20racist%20persecution.%20Faith-based%20persecution%2C%20endorsed%20by%20the%20establishment%2C%20was%20soon%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F978-1-349-19399-8_3%5C%22%3ESociologists%3C%2Fa%3E%20point%20to%20a%201977%20report%20commissioned%20by%20the%20West%20Midlands%20Police%20and%20titled%20Shades%20of%20Grey%20as%20having%20been%20instrumental%20in%20creating%2C%20as%20journalist%20Derek%20Bishton%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fderekbishton.com%2Fshades-of-grey-a-report-on-police-west-indian-relations-in-handsworth%2F%5C%22%3Enotes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20popular%20sentiment%20that%20Black%20people%20were%20much%20more%20predisposed%20to%20criminality%2C%20and%20that%20it%20was%20their%20culture%20which%20produced%20this%20behaviour%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20insidiously%20associated%20%E2%80%9Chardcore%20Dreadlocks%E2%80%9D%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20criminalised%20sub-culture%E2%80%9D.%20It%20asserted%20this%20community%20posed%20a%20constant%20threat%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20peace%20of%20individual%20citizens%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20of%20course%20crime%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20area%2C%20as%20in%20any%20other.%20Indeed%2C%20Zephaniah%20himself%20has%20spoken%20about%20possessing%20a%20gun%20at%20one%20point%20and%20also%20serving%20time%20in%20prison%20for%20burglary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Brown%E2%80%99s%20report%20served%20to%20do%2C%20however%2C%20was%20to%20designate%20this%20criminality%20as%20wholly%20tied%20to%20specific%20cultural%20norms.%20It%20hinged%20on%20a%20thinly%20defined%20and%20spurious%20characterisation%20of%20Rastafari%20as%20a%20criminal%20enterprise%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20spiritual%20movement%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECriminologists%20highlight%20how%20this%20false%20association%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fblack-people-are-often-associated-with-deviance-but-i-never-understood-the-true-impact-until-i-was-racially-profiled-179259%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cdeviance%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Black%20communities%20and%20Black%20culture%20persists%20in%20British%20society%2C%20with%20horrendous%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChallenging%20oppression%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%20rose%20to%20fame%20in%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%20through%20published%20poetry%20and%20subsequent%20musical%20and%20TV%20appearances.%20Through%20his%20titanic%20output%2C%20he%20showed%20Rastafari%20to%20be%20a%20vibrant%20and%20assertive%20movement%2C%20which%20rejected%20violence%20and%20hatred%2C%20and%20challenged%20oppression%20wherever%20it%20resided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%