ions%20repeatedly%20accused%20el-Sissi%20of%20cracking%20down%20on%20promising%20opposition%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHisham%20Kassem%20is%20currently%20in%20prison%20on%20political%20charges%20and%20Ahmed%20Altantawy%20is%20facing%20charges%20while%20dozens%20of%20members%20of%20his%20campaign%20are%20being%20detained%2C%E2%80%9D%20Timothy%20E.%20Kaldas%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20Washington-based%20Tahrir%20Institute%20for%20Middle%20East%20Policy%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20election%20cycle%20for%20Egyptians%20living%20abroad%20concluded%20on%20Saturday.%20Though%20no%20official%20count%20is%20yet%20available%2C%20voter%20turnout%20is%20projected%20to%20be%20lower%20than%20expected%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%E2%80%94%20then%20retracted%20from%20%E2%80%94%20a%20local%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%E2%80%99s%20first%20election%20cycle%20since%20Sisi%E2%80%99s%20government%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1vSRCfeL1L%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F1vSRCfeL1L%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Mada%20Masr%20%D9%85%D8%AF%D9%89%20%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B1%20(%40MadaMasr)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMadaMasr%2Fstatus%2F1731693630849515751%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%204%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expected%20reelection%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20el-Sissi%20is%20unlikely%20to%20face%20much%20international%20criticism%20in%20light%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20current%20war%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20impact%20of%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20classified%20as%20a%20terrorist%20group%20by%20the%20US%2C%20EU%2C%20Germany%20and%20others%2C%20global%20attention%20has%20shifted%20from%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20dire%20human%20rights%20record%2C%20its%20crackdown%20on%20the%20political%20opposition%20and%20the%20poor%20economic%20state%20to%20its%20role%20as%20reliable%20political%20partner%20in%20the%20region%2C%20mediator%20and%20access%20point%20for%20humanitarian%20goods%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20not%20only%20boosted%20el-Sissi%E2%80%99s%20international%20reputation%2C%20but%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20positive%20impact%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20European%20Commission%20announced%20up%20to%20%E2%82%AC9%20billion%20(%249.7%20billion)%20in%20investments%20in%20Egypt%20while%20other%20reports%20indicate%20that%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20is%20considering%20as%20much%20as%20doubling%20the%20size%20of%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20loan%20in%20response%20to%20the%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaldas%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20happens%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20Egypt%20has%20largely%20failed%20to%20fulfill%20its%20reform%20commitments%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20preventing%20the%20IMF%20from%20completing%20a%20review%20and%20disbursing%20loan%20tranches.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20planned%20investments%20and%20loans%20are%20a%20welcome%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20for%20a%20country%20that%20has%20been%20reeling%20from%20an%20economic%20crisis%20since%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Central%20Bank%20of%20Egypt%2C%20inflation%20was%20at%2038%25%20in%20October%2C%20while%20the%20Egyptian%20pound%20has%20lost%20half%20its%20value%20against%20the%20US%20dollar.%20Official%20estimates%20state%20that%2030%25%20of%20the%20population%20live%20in%20poverty.%20Foreign%20reserves%2C%20which%20are%20needed%20to%20pay%20back%20loans%2C%20are%20almost%20depleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20none%20of%20the%20experts%20DW%20spoke%20to%2C%20expect%20any%20major%20international%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20West%20has%20not%20been%20too%20critical%20of%20elections%20in%20Egypt%20either%2C%20and%20el-Sissi%20and%20the%20military%20have%20been%20regularly%20perceived%20in%20the%20West%20as%20the%20only%20actors%20who%20can%20prevent%20chaos%20in%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Christian%20Achrainer%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20Denmark%E2%80%99s%20Roskilde%20University%2C%20who%20has%20extensively%20published%20on%20Egypt%2C%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEgypt%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20a%20volatile%20region%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20not%20only%20Gaza%2C%20but%20also%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20other%20neighboring%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20Sudan%2C%20Libya%20and%20Yemen%E2%80%94%20are%20at%20war%2C%20and%20the%20Red%20Sea%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20becoming%20a%20battlefield%20for%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20proxy%20militias%20against%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20a%20horror%20scenario%20for%20European%20decision-makers%20if%20Egypt%2C%20as%20the%20most%20populous%20North%20African%20and%20Arab%20country%2C%20would%20become%20unstable%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20Achrainer%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20view%20is%20echoed%20by%20Gamal%20Abdel%20Gawad%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20American%20University%20in%20Cairo%20and%20advisor%20to%20the%20Cairo-based%20think%20tank%20Al-Ahram%20Center%20for%20Political%20and%20Strategic%20Studies%20whose%20political%20leanings%20are%20considered%20closely%20aligned%20with%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNeither%20the%20region%20nor%20the%20world%20is%20prepared%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20turbulent%20situation%20in%20Egypt%20due%20to%20an%20economic%20fallout%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gawad%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20view%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20threat%20to%20displace%20Palestinians%20and%20bring%20the%20conflict%20to%20Egypt%2C%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20risk%20to%20the%20Egyptian%20national%20security%20which%20has%20led%20to%20a%20state%20of%20unity%20and%20increased%20support%20for%20the%20president%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Timothy%20Kaldas%2C%20this%20also%20means%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20recent%20softening%20of%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20position%20vis-a-vis%20Sisi%E2%80%99s%20economic%20malpractice%20and%20rights%20violations%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20war%20on%20Gaza%20gives%20further%20reason%20to%20doubt%20the%20needed%20reforms%20are%20on%20the%20horizon.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20chance%20to%20improve%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20human%20rights%20record%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20Mefreh%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Swiss-based%20human%20rights%20watchdog%20Committee%20for%20Justice%2C%20thinks%20that%20one%20scenario%20of%20the%20expected%20reelection%20of%20el-Sissi%20will%20lead%20at%20best%20%E2%80%9Cto%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%20current%20cosmetic%20policies%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20human%20rights.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20regime%20has%20released%20between%201%2C000%20and%201%2C500%20political%20prisoners%20this%20year%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20National%20Dialogue%20and%20political%20opening%2C%20Egyptian%20rights%20groups%20claim%20that%20at%20least%20three%20times%20as%20many%20political%20prisoners%20were%20arrested%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20of%20whom%20continue%20to%20be%20detained%20without%20trial%20or%20even%20charges%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Tahrir%20Institute%E2%80%99s%20Kaldas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%E2%80%99s%20most%20prominent%20political%20prisoner%2C%20Alaa%20Abdel-Fattah%2C%20also%20remains%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20second%20scenario%20is%20a%20return%20to%20direct%20repression%2C%20including%20targeting%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20human%20rights%20organizations%20inside%20Egypt%20and%20in%20exile%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mefreh%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20key%20difference%20will%20be%20whether%20the%20regime%20is%20under%20significant%20pressure%20to%20improve%20the%20human%20rights%20record%20during%20the%20current%20economic%20crisis%2C%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20recent%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Gaza%20has%20shown%20that%20there%20is%20not%20enough%20serious%20pressure%20on%20the%20Egyptian%20regime%2C%20and%20this%20makes%20the%20second%20scenario%20more%20likely%20in%20the%20upcoming%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcould-egypts-presidential-elections-be-a-chance-for-change%2Fa-67647785%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702268798000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11095545%2F339299863_723069192631661_5649768612959447302_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fegypts-presidential-elections-change-in-the-offing-or-much-of-the-same%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sissi's%20reputation%20has%20improved%20somewhat%2C%20observers%20fear%20that%20neither%20Egypt's%20economic%20crisis%20nor%20the%20dire%20human%20rights%20situation%20will%20be%20resolved.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fegypts-presidential-elections-change-in-the-offing-or-much-of-the-same%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gao%20Yaojie%3A%20Dissident%20doctor%20who%20exposed%20China's%20Aids%20epidemic%2C%20dies%20at%2095%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702268724000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F15C81%2Fproduction%2F_127271298_gettyimages-71601629.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.c